<p>I have a contact form which sends an email once submitted and displays an alert successfully when sent. My problem was 1) after its sent the email form still has content. 2) If I refresh the page the email is sent again with the previous details. In order to solve this I used the below code in php which is doing the job of refreshing with out sending an email.</p>  <p><div class="snippet" data-lang="js" data-hide="false"> <div class="snippet-code"> <pre class="snippet-code-js lang-js prettyprint-override"><code>header("Location: contact.php"); exit;</code></pre> </div> </div> </p>  <p>Now my problem is The alert is not displayed anymore which is true because the alert is in my HTML and header refreshes the page and it never reaches the alert in HTML(displayed using php echo). Here is the HTML Code :</p>  <p><div class="snippet" data-lang="js" data-hide="false"> <div class="snippet-code"> <pre class="snippet-code-html lang-html prettyprint-override"><code>&lt;div class="container"&gt;   &lt;div class="row"&gt;     &lt;div class="col-md-6 col-md-offset-3" id="emailForm"&gt;       &lt;h1 class="center"&gt;Email Form&lt;/h1&gt;       &lt;?php echo $result; //header( "Location: contact.php"); //exit; ?&gt;       &lt;p&gt;Please get in touch ! I will get back to you as soon as I can !!&lt;/p&gt;       &lt;form method="post" id="contactForm"&gt;         &lt;div class="form-group"&gt;           &lt;label for="name"&gt;Your Name&lt;/label&gt;           &lt;input type="text" name="name" class="form-control" placeholder="Your Name" value="&lt;?php echo $_POST['name'] ?&gt;" /&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;          &lt;div class="form-group"&gt;           &lt;label for="email"&gt;Your Email&lt;/label&gt;           &lt;input type="email" name="email" class="form-control" placeholder="Your Email" value="&lt;?php echo $_POST['email'] ?&gt;" /&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;          &lt;div class="form-group"&gt;           &lt;label for="message"&gt;Message&lt;/label&gt;           &lt;textarea class="form-control" name="message"&gt;             &lt;?php echo $_POST[ 'message'] ?&gt;           &lt;/textarea&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;         &lt;input type="submit" name="submit" id="send" class="btn btn-success btn-lg center" value="Submit" /&gt;       &lt;/form&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;/div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</code></pre> </div> </div> </p>  <p>Here is the PHP code:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;?php  if($_POST['submit']) {      if(!$_POST['name']){          $error.="&lt;br&gt;Please enter your name";     }     if(!$_POST['email']){          $error.="&lt;br&gt;Please enter your email address";     }     if(!$_POST['message']){          $error.="&lt;br&gt;Please enter a message";     }      if ($_POST['email']!= "" AND !filter_var($_POST['email'], FILTER_VALIDATE_EMAIL)) {          $error.="&lt;br&gt;Please enter a valid email address";     }       if( $error )     {         $result='&lt;div class="alert alert-danger"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;There were error(s):'.$error.'&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;';     }      else {          if(mail("madistackcloud@gmail.com","Message from Deepak", "Name: ".$_POST['name']."Email: ".$_POST['email']."Message: ".$_POST['message'])) {              $result='&lt;div class="alert alert-success alert-dismissible"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Thank you! I\'ll be in touch.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;';              }          else         {             $result='&lt;div class="alert alert-danger alert-dismissible"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Oops! Something went wrong. Please try again !&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;';         }      } } </code></pre>  <p>?></p>  <p>Is there any workaround for this or any other method which can do the job. Kindly help.</p>